Miray's Cleaning, standardizing, and bidsifying data pipeline
This document outlines the scripts used for organizing, standardizing, and converting MRI data into BIDS format. Each section corresponds to one script, with its function and detailed workflow.
PIPELINE OVERVIEW:
[1] Rename raw MRI folders using Name_Info.txt
     └─ bash /Raid/Current/Miray/MRI/codes/codes/cleaning_and_bidsifying/extract_txt.sh
[2] Standardize folder names & group into isolated_measures
     └─ bash /Raid/Current/Miray/MRI/codes/codes/cleaning_and_bidsifying/standardization.sh
          ↓
[3] Standardize DICOM SeriesDescription fields
     └─ bash /Raid/Current/Miray/MRI/codes/codes/cleaning_and_bidsifying/DICOM_seriesdesc_namechange.sh
          ↓
[4] BIDSify DICOMs (convert into BIDS structure)
     └─ bash /Raid/Current/Miray/MRI/codes/codes/cleaning_and_bidsifying/dcm2bids/dcm2bids_miray.sh
          ↓
[4b] Organize and BIDSify .info/.tiff metadata (if present)
     └─ python3 /Raid/Current/Miray/MRI/codes/codes/cleaning_and_bidsifying/Info2JSON.py
          ↓
[5] Rename and move JSON/NIfTI outputs into final BIDS folder
     └─ bash /Raid/Current/Miray/MRI/codes/codes/cleaning_and_bidsifying/renameJSONnii2bidsout.sh

