1. Rename MRI Folders with Name_Info.txt (ONLY FOR OLDER STUDIES)
Command: bash /Raid/Current/Miray/MRI/codes/codes/cleaning_and_bidsifying/extract_txt.sh
This script automates the renaming of MRI scan subfolders based on mappings provided in "Name_Info.txt" files for each participant 
#
#   For every participant directory (e.g., FAAH001), the script:
#     1. Recursively searches for all "Name_Info.txt" files.
#     2. For each mapping file, reads lines of the form:
#         i.e.  Ex01859Se03    ASSET Calibration
#        It attempts to find a subfolder named "Ex01859Se03" in the same
#        directory as the mapping file and renames the subfolder to "ASSET Calibration"
#        (with sanitization to avoid unsafe filesystem characters).
#     3. Handles name conflicts by appending "(1)", "(2)", etc.
#     4. Skips if no matching subfolder exists.
#
# Logging:
#   - A per-participant log is written to:
#         /Raid/Current/CURB174-2020/NOUD-026/xtracting_txt_and_renaming_log/<PARTICIPANT>.log
#   - A master log listing ALL discovered "Name_Info.txt" paths is written to:
#         /Raid/Current/CURB174-2020/NOUD-026/xtracting_txt_and_renaming_log/all_Name_Info_paths.log
