2. Standardize Folder Names & Group into isolated_measures
Command:bash /Raid/Current/Miray/MRI/codes/codes/cleaning_and_bidsifying/standardization.sh

This script scans all participant folders inside a study directory and identifies MRI scan subfolders that match known scan types 
(e.g. Faces, Cards, Resting State, T1, PD). For each match, it copies the folder into a new subfolder called "isolated_measures" inside 
that participant's directory, using a standardized name (e.g. "AxEPI_Faces", "SagT1").
- Creates an isolated_measures folder inside each participant directory.
- Recursively searches for subfolders matching (flexible, case-insensitive): faces, cards, AxEPI … Rest/Resting/Resting State, Sag T1, Obl … Ax … PD
- Copies matches into isolated_measures, preserving names (_1, _2 for duplicates).
- Renames copies into standardized names:
    faces → AxEPI_Faces
    cards → AxEPI_Cards
    AxEPI Rest… → AxEPI_RestingState
    Sag T1 → SagT1
    Obl Ax PD → OblAx_PDfseXL
Original folders remain unchanged.

