5b. Rename and Move JSON/NIfTI Files to BIDS Output
Script:
bash renameJSONnii2bidsout.sh

Description:
Renames and organizes JSON + NIfTI files into BIDS-compliant format.

Workflow:
- Scans only SRC_DIR (non-recursive) for .nii, .nii.gz, .json.
- Copies each file with prefix COPY_.
- Updates JSON 'SeriesDescription' = parent folder name.
- Extracts participant ID (three levels up; uses FAAH### if present).
- Renames files to BIDS convention:
  SagT1_bravo_func → sub-<ID>_T1w
  AxEPI_RestingState → sub-<ID>_task-rest_bold
  AxEPI_Cards → sub-<ID>_task-cards_bold
  AxEPI_Faces → sub-<ID>_task-faces_bold
- Creates participant folder in /home/sklab/miray/bids_apps/BIDS_OUTPUT/<participantID>
- Ensures func/ exists inside participant folder.
- Moves renamed files into func/.
- If NIfTI is .nii, gzips to .nii.gz; leaves as-is if already gzipped.

Notes & Safeguards:
- Non-recursive scan.
- JSON edits with sed.
- Duplicate filenames suffixed _1, _2.
- Logs to STDERR.
